Name: rickrolldetector
Version: 0.1.3
Summary: A module made for rickroll protection
Home-page: https://github.com/Sengolda/rickrolldetector
Author: Sengolda
License: MIT
Description: ### RickRoll detecttor
        - A module made for rickroll protection
        - To install You can use:
            - This is recomended `pip install rickrolldetector`
            - This is for beta testers `pip install git+https://github.com/Sengolda/rickrolldetector`
        
        ##### Examples (sync)
        ```py
        from rickrolldetector import RickRoleFinder
        
        RickRoleFinder.find_rickroll("https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dQw4w9WgXcQ")
        ```
        
        ##### Examples (async)
        ```py
        from rickrolldetector import RickRoleFinder
        import asyncio
        
        async def main():
            await RickRoleFinder.async_find_rickroll("https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dQw4w9WgXcQ")
        
        
        asyncio.run(main())
        ```
        
        ##### Example discord.py rickroll detector bot
        ```py
        import discord
        from discord.ext import commands
        from rickrolldetector import RickRollFinder
        
        RICKROLL_WARN_MESSAGE = "Rickroll found in message."
        
        bot = commands.Bot(command_prefix = ">", intents = discord.Intents.default())
        
        @bot.event
        async def on_ready():
            print("No more rickrolls")
        
        @bot.command()
        async def hi(ctx):
            await ctx.send("hello")
        
        @bot.event
        async def on_message(msg):
            for i in msg.content.split(" "):
                i = i.replace("<","").replace(">", "")
                if "https://" in i and await RickRoleFinder.async_find_rickroll(i):
                    await msg.send(RICKROLL_WARN_MESSAGE)
                    break
            await bot.process_commands(msg)
        
        bot.run("TOKEN HERE")
        ```
